- ## Nueva instalacion usando git  
-  
  ```
  $ git clone https://github.com/odoo/odoo.git
  $ sudo apt install python3 python3-pip
  $ sudo apt install postgresql postgresql-client
#  $ sudo -u postgres createuser -s $USER
#  $ createdb $USER
  $ sudo apt install python3-dev libxml2-dev libxslt1-dev libldap2-dev libsasl2-dev libtiff5-dev libjpeg62-turbo-dev libopenjp2-7-dev zlib1g-dev libfreetype6-dev liblcms2-dev libwebp-dev libharfbuzz-dev libfribidi-dev libxcb1-dev libpq-dev

#	- python3 odoo-bin --addons-path=addons -d mydb
	- python3 odoo-bin --addons-path addons,custom_addons -d mydb  

  $ cd odoo
  $ pip3 install setuptools wheel
  $ pip3 install -r requirements.txt
  $ sudo mkdir custom_addons
  $ sudo chmod 755 custom_addons
  ```
- Archivos importantes  
	- odoo.conf (copiar desde directorio debian a raiz)  
- ### Configurar odoo.conf  
	- db_host = localhost  
	- db_port = 5432  
	- db_user = odoo
	- db_password = odoo  
	- addons_path = /home/vagrant/odoo/addons,/home/vagrant/odoo/custom_addons  



- ### Crear usuario postres
```
$ sudo su postgres
$ createuser --createdb --username postgres --no-createrole --no-superuser --pwprompt vagrant

```

- ### Iniciar servidor 
	- python3 odoo-bin -c odoo.conf -d mydb
	- ./odoo-bin -c odoo.conf -d mydb1
- ### url  
	- http://localhost:8069  
	- user: admin  
	- password: admin  
- ## modulos  
-  
  ```
  $ ./odoo-bin scaffold reto custom_addons/
  $ cd reto
  $ mkdir static
  
  ```
